1. Create Dockerfile
2. docker build .
3. docker run -p 3000:3000 <image_id> ==>>> ERROR
4. docker run --help
5. docker run --interactive --tty or docker run -it <image_id> (Works coorectly)
6. docker ps //To list all the running container
7. docker start <container_name> // again We can't interacte with container
8. docker stop <name of the running container> ==>>>
9. docker start -a <container_name> // There is something doesn't work correctly

TO FIX THAT:

1. docker stop <name of the running container>
2. docker start -a -i <container_name> 
